                            <comment id="13050665" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 19:23:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m still digging in my logs, but it appears that the region server took 40 secs to open a single file from one of the daughters and that&apos;s why the clients eventually ran out of retries. It seems at first that it didn&apos;t retry at all, but now I think we should just have a better error message.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050670" author="stack" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 19:33:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So it did retry? And we just ran out of them?  Yeah better message!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13052893" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2011 22:23:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk and branch the new error messages. Doesn&apos;t change any behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13056855" author="hudson" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2011 22:42:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #1995 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/HBase-TRUNK/1995/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/HBase-TRUNK/1995/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15015757" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 11:52:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
